A man can disappear from public view for nearly a month, keep collecting a taxpayer-funded paycheck, receive world-class healthcare, and enjoy guaranteed leave...

...while millions of Americans are told those exact benefits are economically impossible. 

What a fucking miracle.

The most impressive thing Fuckhead Mitch McConnell ever built wasn't legislation.

It was a political system where politicians can spend decades explaining why ordinary people don't deserve basic security... then personally enjoy every single benefit the second they need it. 

That's not irony. That's industrial-scale hypocrisy.

Imagine telling a warehouse worker:

"Sorry, paid leave isn't realistic."

Then watching a senator vanish for weeks while still collecting a salary, healthcare, and job security. 

Apparently socialism is a dangerous threat to freedom right up until it's happening directly to the people warning us about it.

It's amazing how quickly "personal responsibility" transforms into "please spare no expense" when the patient has a Senate office and a government pension. 

The ladder always seems to disappear right after they climb it.

Hopefully the motherfucker suffers.

